      Tools (F12) -> Network tab.
       * Perform a login attempt.
       * Click on the login request (in red).
       * Look at the Response tab. It will show the
         exact error message coming from Laravel. If
         it's a CORS error, you will see a message
         like "CORS policy: No
         'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header is
         present".
   3. Frontend API URL: Your frontend is configured
      to call http://127.0.0.1:8000/api. Ensure this
      matches exactly where your backend is
      listening.
   4. Axios Header: If you are still seeing an error,
      check if the XMLHttpRequest header is being
      sent correctly in the browser's Network tab for
      the preflight (OPTIONS) request.

